Subject: [PATCH] ui: Mods loader — inject Mod CSS/JS into WebUI pages

Implements the FennecModLoader which reads installed Mods from the
SQLite Mods registry (src/mods/) and injects their CSS and JS into
the appropriate fennec:// WebUI pages at page load time.

Injection order per page:
  1. tokens.css (base tokens, always first)
  2. Active theme Mod token overrides (from manifest.json "tokens" block)
  3. Active theme Mod CSS files (in manifest order)
  4. Active UI Mod CSS files
  5. Active UI Mod JS entry points (sandboxed — no page content access)

The loader respects the "surfaces" declaration in each Mod's manifest:
a Mod targeting ["sidebar"] is only injected into fennec://sidebar.

window.__fennec.ui API is exposed only in WebUI contexts where a Mod
with type="ui" is active. Page content never sees this API.

TODO: Stub. Full implementation in Phase 2.
      Tracked: fennec-browser/fennec#18

PILLAR: Customization
JOURNAL: none — Mod loading is local. If a Mod declares
         makes_network_requests=true it is rejected at registry
         validation time and never installed.
